{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.20",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 20 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:1",
      "text": "Then answered Zophar the Naamathite, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:2",
      "text": "Therefore do my thoughts cause me to answer, and for this I make haste.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:3",
      "text": "I have heard the check of my reproach, and the spirit of my understanding causeth me to answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:4",
      "text": "Knowest thou not this of old, since man was placed upon earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:5",
      "text": "That the triumphing of the wicked is short, and the joy of the hypocrite but for a moment?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:6",
      "text": "Though his excellency mount up to the heavens, and his head reach unto the clouds;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:7",
      "text": "Yet he shall perish for ever like his own dung: they which have seen him shall say, Where is he?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:8",
      "text": "He shall fly away as a dream, and shall not be found: yea, he shall be chased away as a vision of the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:9",
      "text": "The eye also which saw him shall see him no more; neither shall his place any more behold him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:10",
      "text": "His children shall seek to please the poor, and his hands shall restore their goods.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:11",
      "text": "His bones are full of the sin of his youth, which shall lie down with him in the dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:12",
      "text": "Though wickedness be sweet in his mouth, though he hide it under his tongue;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:13",
      "text": "Though he spare it, and forsake it not; but keep it still within his mouth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:14",
      "text": "Yet his meat in his bowels is turned, it is the gall of asps within him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:15",
      "text": "He hath swallowed down riches, and he shall vomit them up again: God shall cast them out of his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:16",
      "text": "He shall suck the poison of asps: the viper’s tongue shall slay him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:17",
      "text": "He shall not see the rivers, the floods, the brooks of honey and butter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:18",
      "text": "That which he laboured for shall he restore, and shall not swallow it down: according to his substance shall the restitution be, and he shall not rejoice therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:19",
      "text": "Because he hath oppressed and hath forsaken the poor; because he hath violently taken away an house which he builded not;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:20",
      "text": "Surely he shall not feel quietness in his belly, he shall not save of that which he desired.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:21",
      "text": "There shall none of his meat be left; therefore shall no man look for his goods.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:22",
      "text": "In the fulness of his sufficiency he shall be in straits: every hand of the wicked shall come upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:23",
      "text": "When he is about to fill his belly, God shall cast the fury of his wrath upon him, and shall rain it upon him while he is eating.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:24",
      "text": "He shall flee from the iron weapon, and the bow of steel shall strike him through.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:25",
      "text": "It is drawn, and cometh out of the body; yea, the glittering sword cometh out of his gall: terrors are upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:26",
      "text": "All darkness shall be hid in his secret places: a fire not blown shall consume him; it shall go ill with him that is left in his tabernacle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:27",
      "text": "The heaven shall reveal his iniquity; and the earth shall rise up against him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:28",
      "text": "The increase of his house shall depart, and his goods shall flow away in the day of his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.20.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:29",
      "text": "This is the portion of a wicked man from God, and the heritage appointed unto him by God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
